Statistic tests

Compare mussels with 5 and 15 rings

## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  diam_15 and diam_5
## t = 33.5, df = 196, p-value <2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is greater than 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.23316     Inf
## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y 
##   0.45626   0.21101

Mussels with 15 rings have greater diameter than mussels with 5 rings (t = 33.51651, df = 196, p-value < 2e-16)
